org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.phd

Class AbstractPhdBallVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.phd.AbstractPhdBallVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PhdBallVisitor

    public abstract class AbstractPhdBallVisitor
extends Object
implements PhdBallVisitor
    AbstractPhdBallVisitor is a PhdBallVisitor that implements all the methods with default implementations that don't do anything. This code is meant to be extended so users don't have to implement any methods that they do not care about (users must override any method that want to handle).
    Author:
    dkatzel

      • visitFileComment

        public void visitFileComment(String comment)
        Ignores the file comment. Optional comment at the beginning of new versions of phd.ball files. The comment is often the path to the corresponding wrapped input file (path to fastq or sff file).
        Specified by:
        visitFileComment in interface PhdBallVisitor
        Parameters:
        comment - the comment at the beginning of the phd file.

      • visitPhd

        public PhdVisitor visitPhd(PhdBallVisitorCallback callback,
                           String id,
                           Integer version)
        Always skips this read.
        Specified by:
        visitPhd in interface PhdBallVisitor
        Parameters:
        callback - the PhdBallVisitorCallback instance that can be used to call pack to the parser.
        id - the id of this phd record.
        version - the version of this phd record; if the version is not specified, then this value will be null. More recent versions of the phdball file format specification allow the version to be included for each record but not all files contain this information.
        Returns:
        null a non-null PhdVisitor instance if this record should be parsed; or null if this phd record should be skipped.
